<p>
  <span class="nym">Elias</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Hebrew</span> <i>אליהו</i> 'Yahweh is God'.  The most common medieval forms were influenced by <span class="lang">Latin</span> <i>(H)elias</i>, deriving from the <span class="lang">Greek</span> form <i>Ἠλίας</i>.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a Biblical prophet and a 4th C martyr. Wycliffite Bible (1395): <i>Elie</i>.</p>
</div>
  
  


